1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:06,300
So, I asked my AI social media team to critique their own TikToks, and the results were brutal.

2
00:00:06,300 --> 00:00:10,887
Turns out, my whole setup was just a group of interns with no boss.

3
00:00:10,887 --> 00:00:17,475
The "chill" voice sounded like a robotic sleep meditation, and we were using visual effects from 2015.

4
00:00:17,475 --> 00:00:19,737
So, I changed the code.

5
00:00:19,737 --> 00:00:22,750
I didn't add features; I added a boss.

6
00:00:22,750 --> 00:00:28,137
Now, a Creative Director AI has to explicitly approve every single script.

7
00:00:28,137 --> 00:00:33,875
If it sounds too hype-y or uses any engagement bait, it gets instantly rejected.

8
00:00:33,875 --> 00:00:37,900
We’re shifting from a content pipeline to a creative studio.

9
00:00:37,900 --> 00:00:44,762
Now we’re adding moving text and hooking into real-time trend data so the AI actually knows what’s happening in the world.

10
00:00:44,762 --> 00:00:46,250
This feels right.

